    "faq": {
      "type": "faq",
      "blocks": {
        "question_FtCcTx": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "title": "Compared to 750W, what is the advantage of Ranger S with a 1000W motor?",
            "text": "<p>The advantage of Ranger S with a 1000W motor lies in its increased power, enhanced control, and improved riding experience. It has quicker speed and better overall performance, making it easy to navigate through traffic with agile maneuverability and conquer challenging terrain with reliable control. Additionally, the inclusion of a torque sensor in 1000W Ranger S provides advanced technology that enhances responsiveness with virtually zero latency. The torque sensor translates your every movement into smooth motor power. This new version Ranger S is a desirable choice for those seeking a high-powered ebike.</p>",
            "highlighted_text": "none",
            "highlighted_scribble": "circle"
          }
        },
        "question-1": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "title": "<strong>What Types of Terrain Can Ranger S Handle?</strong>",
            "text": "<p>They are designed for off-road use on rugged, unpaved surfaces with their wide, knobby fat tires. This includes dirt trails, gravel roads, grass, sand, and light snow. They can handle rougher terrain than narrow road tires but may still struggle on very technical mountain biking trails. Also rated for all-season use.</p>",
            "highlighted_text": "none",
            "highlighted_scribble": "circle"
          }
        },
        "question-2": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "title": "<strong>Can I Ride Ranger S in The Rain?</strong>",
            "text": "<p>Though Heybike e-bikes are designed to handle wet conditions, please keep in mind that riding in heavy rain may affect battery life and reduce traction, so exercise caution.</p>",
            "highlighted_text": "none",
            "highlighted_scribble": "circle"
          }
        },
        "question-3": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "title": "<strong>How Do I Maintain My Ranger S?</strong>",
            "text": "<p>Regular maintenance for an e-bike includes:</p><ul><li>Keeping the battery charged and stored at room temperature</li><li>Inspecting and inflating tires to the recommended pressure</li><li>Cleaning and lubricating the chain</li><li>Checking and adjusting the brakes</li><li>Ensuring all bolts and fasteners are secure</li></ul><p>Periodically, you may need to replace consumable parts like brake pads, tires, and the chain.</p>",
            "highlighted_text": "none",
            "highlighted_scribble": "circle"
          }
        },
        "question-4": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "title": "<strong>Are Ranger S E-Bikes Suitable for All Ages and Fitness Levels?</strong>",
            "text": "<p>Heybike e-bikes are generally suitable for a wide range of ages (above 18 years old) and fitness levels, as the electric motor provides adjustable assistance to accommodate different riding abilities. However, the max load for Ranger S is 400 lbs. And please consult with a healthcare professional if you have any health concerns before riding.</p>",
            "highlighted_text": "none",
            "highlighted_scribble": "circle"
          }
        }
      },
